The Board of Directors, Custodian and Allied Insurance Limited, has appointed Mr. Edeki Isujeh as Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer, following the approval of the National Insurance Commission (NAICOM). Isujeh has over 30 years of experience in the insurance industry, having worked in different insurance companies in insurance operations, sales/business development and general management. At Custodian, he has at various times coordinated the marketing and technical operations of the company. As a result of his commitment and hard work, he was appointed executive director of the company in 2016. He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Insurance from the University of Lagos and is a member of the Chartered Insurance Institute, London. Aside from various technical courses, he attended in and outside Nigeria, he has over the years attended management courses preparing him for leadership roles. He is an alumnus of the Lagos Business School as well as the prestigious Wharton Business School, the USA where he attended Executive programmes. Mr. Edeki Isujeh was announced as the Managing Director of Custodian and Allied Insurance Limited following the retirement of the erstwhile Managing Director, Mr. Toye Odunsi, in December 2020.